{
  "bookId": "laozi-boshu",
  "num": 28,
  "title": "第二十八章（恆德）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "知亓雄，守亓雌，為天下溪。為天下溪，恆德不離。恆德不離，復歸嬰兒。"
    },
    {
      "text": "知亓白，守亓辱，為天下浴。為天下浴，恆德乃足。德乃足，復歸於樸。"
    },
    {
      "text": "知亓白，守亓黑，為天下式。為天下式，恆德不忒。恆德不忒，復歸於无極。"
    },
    {
      "text": "樸散則為器，聖人用則為官長。夫大制无割。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 33,
          "end": 33
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "雄以喻尊，雌以喻卑。人雖自知其尊顯，當復守之以卑微，去雄之強梁，就雌之柔和，如是則天下歸之，如水流入深谿也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 33,
          "end": 33
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "人能謙下如深谿，則德常在，不復離於己。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 33,
          "end": 33
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "當復歸志於嬰兒，惷然而無所知也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 23,
          "end": 24
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "白以喻昭昭，黑以喻默默。人雖自知昭昭，明白當復守之以默默，如闇昧無所見，如是則可為天下法式，則德常在。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 37,
          "end": 38
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "人能為天下法式，則德常在於己，不復差忒。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 53,
          "end": 54
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "德不差忒，則常生久壽，歸身於無窮極也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 32,
          "end": 32
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "榮以喻尊貴，辱以喻污濁。人能知己之有榮貴，當復守之以污濁，如是則天下歸之，如水流入深谷也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 32,
          "end": 32
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "足，止也。人能為天下谷，則德乃常止於己。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-9",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 42,
          "end": 43
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "復當歸身於質樸，不復為文飾。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-10",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 1
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "器，用也。萬物之樸散則為器用也。若道散則為神明，流為日月，分為五行也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-11",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 20,
          "end": 20
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "聖人升用則為百官之元長也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-12",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 20,
          "end": 20
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "聖人用之則以大道制御天下，無所傷割，治身則以大道制御情欲，不害精神也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ],
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 33,
          "end": 33
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "雄，先之屬；雌，後之屬也。知為天下之先也，必後也，是以聖人後其身而身先也。谿不求物而物自歸之，嬰兒不用智而合自然之智。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 23,
          "end": 24
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "式，模則也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 37,
          "end": 38
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "忒，差也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 53,
          "end": 54
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "不可窮也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 34,
          "end": 34
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "此三者，言常反終，後乃德全其所處也。下章云，反者道之動也。功不可取，常處其母也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 20,
          "end": 20
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "樸，真也。真散則百行出，殊類生，若器也。聖人因其分散，故為之立官長。以善為師，不善為資，移風易俗，復使歸於一也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 20,
          "end": 20
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "大制者，以天下之心為心，故無割也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
